<p>I have a sample wpf app here and wondering, why BMP is loading faster than PNG. Here is the exact setup: </p>  <pre><code>- Windows 7 - Visual Studio 2013 - landscape.png, 1920x1080, 2.4mb - landscape.bmp, 1920x1080, 5.6mb - wpf-app, class MainWindow.xaml.cs constructor, no other code before </code></pre>  <p>Code: </p>  <pre><code>var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew(); var Bitmap1 = new Bitmap("landscape.bmp"); long t1 = sw.ElapsedMilliseconds;  sw.Restart(); var Bitmap2 = new Bitmap("landscape.png"); long t2 = sw.ElapsedMilliseconds; </code></pre>  <p>So the BMP loads with around 6ms, the PNG needs 40ms. </p>  <p>Why is that so?</p>